      "content": "i see. so the research basically backs the school up then? it feels like the parents who are worried are just being labeled as \"anti-science\" or something, but a lot of them feel like they are just trying to protect their kids' innocence or their own religious values. isn't it also a valid scientific or philosophical argument that kids maybe shouldn't be exposed to these concepts until they're older? why does the research seem to only favor the school's perspective?",
